\begin{align*}
z = a(\cos \theta + i\sin \theta)
\end{align*}

Then, $z^5 = a^5(\cos(5\theta) + i\sin(5\theta))$
for $\overline{z}$, we get:
\begin{align*}
\overline{z} = a(\cos(-\theta) + i\sin(-\theta))
